1047
00:57:50,810 --> 00:57:52,780
We're not just an event that happens.

1048
00:57:52,780 --> 00:57:56,310
We are now part of the city's art scene.

1049
00:57:56,310 --> 00:57:58,920
I don't think any other
convention anywhere

1050
00:57:58,920 --> 00:58:00,370
has that sort of distinction.

1051
00:58:01,606 --> 00:58:04,273
(drums banging)

1052
00:58:17,917 --> 00:58:19,480
- [Bubbles] I hate going on stage.

1053
00:58:19,480 --> 00:58:21,083
I get stage-fright hardcore.

1054
00:58:22,320 --> 00:58:23,980
And people are like, you're the con chair.

1055
00:58:23,980 --> 00:58:25,410
You have to be extroverted.

1056
00:58:25,410 --> 00:58:27,520
You have to be willing to talk to anybody

1057
00:58:27,520 --> 00:58:28,580
and talk about anything.

1058
00:58:28,580 --> 00:58:29,413
And I'm not.

1059
00:58:32,630 --> 00:58:35,113
The suit definitely helps with that.

1060
00:58:39,610 --> 00:58:42,720
I love being in a costume
and being able to act

1061
00:58:42,720 --> 00:58:44,130
like something else,
'cause in high school,

1062
00:58:44,130 --> 00:58:45,330
I was the school mascot.

1063
00:58:48,570 --> 00:58:52,843
I'm more open and comfortable with myself.

1064
00:58:58,680 --> 00:59:00,750
- Since I was like three years old,

1065
00:59:00,750 --> 00:59:03,210
I was trying to take a feather duster

1066
00:59:03,210 --> 00:59:04,430
and put it in my shorts.

1067
00:59:04,430 --> 00:59:05,940
And then I have a tail.

1068
00:59:05,940 --> 00:59:08,250
If you found a mask with feathers on it,

1069
00:59:08,250 --> 00:59:10,640
possibilities were endless.

1070
00:59:10,640 --> 00:59:13,290
So I was just trying to
make the perfect costume.

1071
00:59:13,290 --> 00:59:15,120
And I found furries where

1072
00:59:15,120 --> 00:59:17,320
we're all trying to get
the perfect costume.

1073
00:59:19,460 --> 00:59:21,440
I had just gotten out of high school

1074
00:59:21,440 --> 00:59:23,100
and I was starting to go to college,

1075
00:59:23,100 --> 00:59:25,293
and I'm making a fursuit for some reason,

1076
00:59:26,240 --> 00:59:28,660
I called a friend up and I was like,

1077
00:59:28,660 --> 00:59:30,170
take me to PetSmart.

1078
00:59:30,170 --> 00:59:33,303
I need to buy a collar in my costume.

1079
00:59:37,050 --> 00:59:39,630
As we're driving back
home, there's this carwash.

1080
00:59:39,630 --> 00:59:41,470
And we just see this guy hopping around,

1081
00:59:41,470 --> 00:59:44,120
struggling to get people
to come to the carwash.

1082
00:59:44,120 --> 00:59:47,440
And I was like, he needs my help.

1083
00:59:47,440 --> 00:59:49,590
I jumped in, I was doing jumping jacks

1084
00:59:49,590 --> 00:59:52,370
and just helping to get a
bunch of people to pull over.

1085
00:59:52,370 --> 00:59:54,163
And it was a success.

1086
00:59:57,020 --> 00:59:59,300
People were like, where did you get that?

1087
00:59:59,300 --> 01:00:00,810
And then when they'd find out I made it,

1088
01:00:00,810 --> 01:00:02,380
they were like, can you make me one?

1089
01:00:02,380 --> 01:00:05,743
And I was like, oh, well, I don't know.

1090
01:00:11,430 --> 01:00:13,680
- I was obsessed with "The Lion King,"

1091
01:00:13,680 --> 01:00:16,930
obsessed with pretty
much any animal movie.

1092
01:00:16,930 --> 01:00:18,620
So I built my first suit at 17

1093
01:00:18,620 --> 01:00:20,943
and I wore it for Halloween
at my high school.

1094
01:00:22,820 --> 01:00:24,150
I went to college, got my degree

1095
01:00:24,150 --> 01:00:25,740
in something completely unrelated

1096
01:00:25,740 --> 01:00:27,740
and was just doing it on the side.

1097
01:00:27,740 --> 01:00:30,660
And then it just kind of
accidentally became a business.

1098
01:00:30,660 --> 01:00:32,323
And now I'm doing this full time.

1099
01:00:35,009 --> 01:00:37,780
- I would see the suits
being built and I'm like,

1100
01:00:37,780 --> 01:00:38,613
I want to do that.

1101
01:00:38,613 --> 01:00:40,230
I could get involved.

1102
01:00:40,230 --> 01:00:42,680
And I didn't really feel
very much technology

1103
01:00:42,680 --> 01:00:45,030
was really being used in
building these things.

1104
01:00:46,358 --> 01:00:47,191
It was a challenge for me.

1105
01:00:47,191 --> 01:00:49,353
I wanted to figure out
how to do it my way.

1106
01:01:08,090 --> 01:01:10,300
- My whole life, I struggled
with anxiety and depression,

1107
01:01:10,300 --> 01:01:13,390
and a few years ago I was
diagnosed with bipolar as well.

1108
01:01:13,390 --> 01:01:15,380
It's really hard and
it just tears you down,

1109
01:01:15,380 --> 01:01:18,370
and I would come home
from work everyday crying.

1110
01:01:18,370 --> 01:01:20,990
Nowadays, I feel like
I've done something good.

1111
01:01:20,990 --> 01:01:23,720
I'm creating something
for someone to enjoy.

1112
01:01:23,720 --> 01:01:26,903
I'm much more stable mentally,
and it feels really good.

1113
01:01:29,998 --> 01:01:33,390
- I had worked really
hard to have a nice house,

1114
01:01:33,390 --> 01:01:36,410
a nice car, typical American dream,

1115
01:01:36,410 --> 01:01:37,900
but I found it was really empty.

1116
01:01:37,900 --> 01:01:39,700
And I found that it
was, this is, you know,

1117
01:01:39,700 --> 01:01:42,210
it was not fulfilling
at the end of the day.

1118
01:01:42,210 --> 01:01:44,920
And I've been having
more fun in doing this

1119
01:01:44,920 --> 01:01:48,393
than I think I've ever had with
anything in my entire life.

1120
01:01:52,990 --> 01:01:54,600
- [Lucky Coyote] I teamed up with Scuff,

1121
01:01:54,600 --> 01:01:56,160
'cause Scuff was starting to build

1122
01:01:56,160 --> 01:01:57,733
pieces and parts on his own.

1123
01:01:58,600 --> 01:02:00,910
- Not only do you want
a fursuit to look good,

1124
01:02:00,910 --> 01:02:02,720
it needs to feel good.

1125
01:02:02,720 --> 01:02:05,720
Every fur suit we build is custom,

1126
01:02:05,720 --> 01:02:07,200
but that's your fursuit.

1127
01:02:07,200 --> 01:02:09,923
It should feel like your
fursuit when you put it on.

1128
01:02:11,600 --> 01:02:15,380
- I think we've made over 600 fursuits.

1129
01:02:15,380 --> 01:02:17,719
I've kind of lost track.

1130
01:02:17,719 --> 01:02:20,636
(crowd chattering)

1131
01:02:26,950 --> 01:02:28,490
- [Announcer] If you can see the camera,

1132
01:02:28,490 --> 01:02:30,020
you're in the picture.

1133
01:02:30,020 --> 01:02:31,770
All right, let's see those paws up.

1134
01:02:43,340 --> 01:02:45,570
- It's not just about
the animal characters.

1135
01:02:45,570 --> 01:02:48,280
It's about the people and
it's about the, you know,

1136
01:02:48,280 --> 01:02:51,020
the atmosphere of it.

1137
01:02:51,020 --> 01:02:53,130
You've got writers, artists, animators,

1138
01:02:53,130 --> 01:02:55,700
performers, musicians that all collide

1139
01:02:55,700 --> 01:02:57,900
into this one massive group.

1140
01:02:57,900 --> 01:03:00,120
And that's what makes it interesting.

1141
01:03:00,120 --> 01:03:02,210
There's always something new.

1142
01:03:02,210 --> 01:03:04,800
My daughter was in the fursuit parade.

1143
01:03:04,800 --> 01:03:07,130
People complimented her on her suit,

1144
01:03:07,130 --> 01:03:08,630
thought she was adorable.

1145
01:03:08,630 --> 01:03:10,910
You want your child to have
as many of those moments

1146
01:03:10,910 --> 01:03:13,550
as they can, 'cause in the adult world,

1147
01:03:13,550 --> 01:03:17,540
you know, you can't
guarantee that for them.

1148
01:03:17,540 --> 01:03:20,440
- [Interviewer] The talent, he's a, whoa.

1149
01:03:20,440 --> 01:03:23,020
We don't know nearly enough about furries.

1150
01:03:23,020 --> 01:03:23,853
We're trying to learn.

1151
01:03:23,853 --> 01:03:24,686
Excellent.

1152
01:03:24,686 --> 01:03:26,328
- Get in touch with Mark Merlino.

1153
01:03:26,328 --> 01:03:28,580
- [Interviewer] He's the
man, he the man, yeah.

1154
01:03:28,580 --> 01:03:32,160
- The earliest media
coverage that I can remember

1155
01:03:32,160 --> 01:03:36,140
was in 1993.

1156
01:03:36,140 --> 01:03:39,150
The crew from Sci-Fi
channel called Sci-Fi Buzz

1157
01:03:39,150 --> 01:03:42,760
wound up going to one of
the early ConFurences.

1158
01:03:42,760 --> 01:03:44,963
And they did a very positive piece.

1159
01:03:46,040 --> 01:03:49,310
We weren't as careful as
people are these days,

1160
01:03:49,310 --> 01:03:51,600
so if people got it wrong,

1161
01:03:51,600 --> 01:03:54,250
I quite often would just let it slide.

1162
01:03:54,250 --> 01:03:55,923
I sometimes regret that.

1163
01:03:59,560 --> 01:04:01,013
- [Mark] This is 2001.

1164
01:04:02,406 --> 01:04:04,400
If you look through it,

1165
01:04:04,400 --> 01:04:06,930
you'll see a lot of photos of furries

1166
01:04:06,930 --> 01:04:09,480
enjoying themselves in fur meets,

1167
01:04:09,480 --> 01:04:13,593
and people are talking about
their own take on furry.

1168
01:04:14,610 --> 01:04:17,240
Interspersed with other articles

1169
01:04:17,240 --> 01:04:21,573
talking about poly groups and
orgies and stuff like that.

1170
01:04:22,880 --> 01:04:26,093
That's not what furry
fandom was all about.

1171
01:04:27,180 --> 01:04:29,550
- I was approached in 99 by a guy

1172
01:04:29,550 --> 01:04:31,140
claiming to be a film student.

1173
01:04:31,140 --> 01:04:33,060
I thought, you know, I'd help
him with this film project.

1174
01:04:33,060 --> 01:04:35,530
So I just answered a few questions

1175
01:04:35,530 --> 01:04:40,530
and ended up at on MTV in
a rather unsavory show.

1176
01:04:44,880 --> 01:04:49,830
- What was even worse was
the CSI episode in 2003.

1177
01:04:49,830 --> 01:04:54,100
They actually had locals
on the show as consultants

1178
01:04:54,100 --> 01:04:56,640
who say that the show decided to

1179
01:04:56,640 --> 01:04:58,430
ignore everything they said,

1180
01:04:58,430 --> 01:05:02,620
- Unfortunately, that was
the image that was now given.

1181
01:05:02,620 --> 01:05:05,870
This is what the world was seeing.

1182
01:05:05,870 --> 01:05:08,230
A boss would see at a clip
somewhere on the news.

1183
01:05:08,230 --> 01:05:10,160
Oh, you're one of those
weird freaky people

1184
01:05:10,160 --> 01:05:11,820
I heard about.

1185
01:05:11,820 --> 01:05:16,220
Some folk lost jobs, lost relationships.

1186
01:05:16,220 --> 01:05:20,720
- I had people at Disney
telling me that I had to leave

1187
01:05:20,720 --> 01:05:24,091
in order to focus on
my career or you know,

1188
01:05:24,091 --> 01:05:27,680
or else I wouldn't have
a career in animation.

1189
01:05:27,680 --> 01:05:30,215
And so I had to make a
decision and that decision

1190
01:05:30,215 --> 01:05:35,215
was to leave the fandom
to focus on a career.

1191
01:05:36,090 --> 01:05:38,590
- You don't tell your family,
you don't tell your work,

1192
01:05:38,590 --> 01:05:40,113
you don't tell other people.

1193
01:05:41,200 --> 01:05:46,200
- That definitely made
for a insular environment,

1194
01:05:46,400 --> 01:05:49,520
especially in the early 2000s.

1195
01:05:49,520 --> 01:05:52,500
- And you, you need to sell
your magazine or something.

1196
01:05:52,500 --> 01:05:55,620
You want people to pick
that thing up and read it.

1197
01:05:55,620 --> 01:05:57,830
Well, you can talk to
this person for 45 minutes

1198
01:05:57,830 --> 01:06:00,590
about, oh, I made this fursuit
and it took me this long,

1199
01:06:00,590 --> 01:06:02,640
and here's how I stitched
it, and this is the.

1200
01:06:02,640 --> 01:06:04,670
You can talk to this guy over here.

1201
01:06:04,670 --> 01:06:06,630
Well, yeah, I'm a writer, I write stories.

1202
01:06:06,630 --> 01:06:08,640
And then my stories are all about furries,

1203
01:06:08,640 --> 01:06:10,850
and I put furries in
the stories and I write.

1204
01:06:10,850 --> 01:06:12,500
Or you get the guy who says yeah,

1205
01:06:12,500 --> 01:06:15,390
I like to have sex in my fursuit.

1206
01:06:15,390 --> 01:06:17,250
That's what's gonna sell.

1207
01:06:17,250 --> 01:06:18,900
Damned if I'm going to stand around

1208
01:06:18,900 --> 01:06:21,720
and let you put this TV show on

1209
01:06:21,720 --> 01:06:23,470
that's going to make them embarrassed

1210
01:06:23,470 --> 01:06:26,030
to be a part of this remarkable thing

1211
01:06:26,030 --> 01:06:27,530
that we have created together.

1212
01:06:28,640 --> 01:06:30,690
So I fought back.

1213
01:06:30,690 --> 01:06:33,550
Here is the problem we face.

1214
01:06:33,550 --> 01:06:37,310
The media wants to do
stories on furry fandom.

1215
01:06:37,310 --> 01:06:41,740
Very, very often, they are
going to be asking questions.

1216
01:06:41,740 --> 01:06:44,000
Does that sort of thing
go on at your convention?

1217
01:06:44,000 --> 01:06:46,300
Look, I run the thing.

1218
01:06:46,300 --> 01:06:48,490
If that sort of thing was
going on in my convention,

1219
01:06:48,490 --> 01:06:52,110
number one, I would like
to think I know about it.

1220
01:06:52,110 --> 01:06:54,213
Number two, why am I not invited?

1221
01:06:56,580 --> 01:06:57,440
Yeah, you're all laughing.

1222
01:06:57,440 --> 01:06:58,830
Ha ha, it's a joke.

1223
01:06:58,830 --> 01:07:00,180
You notice I didn't say no?

1224
01:07:01,960 --> 01:07:03,620
Never lie.

1225
01:07:03,620 --> 01:07:06,280
But you can minimize it.

1226
01:07:06,280 --> 01:07:09,530
- Anthrocon is not just
for people in costume.

1227
01:07:09,530 --> 01:07:12,350
It's for artists, cartoonists, performers,

1228
01:07:12,350 --> 01:07:14,750
and we have writers, artists, puppeteers,

1229
01:07:14,750 --> 01:07:16,170
and there'll be wandering about.

1230
01:07:16,170 --> 01:07:18,630
If you see a large raccoon
on the streets of Pittsburgh,

1231
01:07:18,630 --> 01:07:19,960
Don't be alarmed, it's just us.

1232
01:07:19,960 --> 01:07:21,250
If they're gonna have
their misconceptions,

1233
01:07:21,250 --> 01:07:24,423
the only thing we can do is
stand back and say, here we are.

1234
01:07:25,830 --> 01:07:27,450
- [Michele Light] Kage is
always is out there talking

1235
01:07:27,450 --> 01:07:29,250
about the money we bring to the city

1236
01:07:29,250 --> 01:07:31,740
and the good will we bring to the city.

1237
01:07:31,740 --> 01:07:33,240
- He knew how to make furry

1238
01:07:33,240 --> 01:07:35,270
appealing to the public at large.

1239
01:07:35,270 --> 01:07:37,460
And it is just so gratifying and rewarding

1240
01:07:37,460 --> 01:07:40,310
to come to a place where
you're welcome and embraced.

1241
01:07:40,310 --> 01:07:41,980
- Yes. Welcome to opening ceremonies

1242
01:07:41,980 --> 01:07:44,890
of what looks to continue to be

1243
01:07:44,890 --> 01:07:47,524
the largest and furriest
convention in the world.

1244
01:07:48,897 --> 01:07:50,410
- Everybody's scared of saying it.

1245
01:07:50,410 --> 01:07:52,470
It's fine, sex is fine.

1246
01:07:52,470 --> 01:07:54,760
And sometimes we have it.

1247
01:07:54,760 --> 01:07:56,520
It's not what defines the community,

1248
01:07:56,520 --> 01:07:57,850
but it's part of the community.

1249
01:07:57,850 --> 01:07:59,330
And for a lot of people,

1250
01:07:59,330 --> 01:08:03,210
this community helped them
discover what that means.

1251
01:08:03,210 --> 01:08:06,580
How could you just try
to say it doesn't exist?

1252
01:08:06,580 --> 01:08:08,100
That's insane.

1253
01:08:08,100 --> 01:08:10,610
- I've been accused of
whitewashing the fandom.

1254
01:08:10,610 --> 01:08:13,960
I've been accused of, oh, he's
trying to control the media.

1255
01:08:13,960 --> 01:08:15,080
Well, you know what?

1256
01:08:15,080 --> 01:08:16,760
You try it someday.

1257
01:08:16,760 --> 01:08:18,630
You know, let's get you
in front of a camera

1258
01:08:18,630 --> 01:08:19,880
and have them say, okay,

1259
01:08:19,880 --> 01:08:22,510
so what's it like to
have sex in a fursuit?

1260
01:08:22,510 --> 01:08:24,310
Let's have you answer that question.

1261
01:08:25,260 --> 01:08:27,910
Especially if you know that
your grandmom's watching.

1262
01:08:29,080 --> 01:08:33,737
Or your mom or your dad
or your future spouse.

1263
01:08:35,130 --> 01:08:38,500
(audience claps)

1264
01:08:38,500 --> 01:08:41,280
When furry fandom first began,

1265
01:08:41,280 --> 01:08:44,460
it was organized by some fellows who,

1266
01:08:44,460 --> 01:08:47,000
as enthusiastic as they were,

1267
01:08:47,000 --> 01:08:51,680
really did not pay much mind
to the sort of public image

1268
01:08:51,680 --> 01:08:54,670
they were giving to
this burgeoning fandom.

1269
01:08:54,670 --> 01:08:55,550
Let's face it.

1270
01:08:55,550 --> 01:08:56,890
I was there.

1271
01:08:56,890 --> 01:08:59,623
Kind of looked like pride
fest on an acid trip.

1272
01:09:03,359 --> 01:09:05,950
(fireworks booming)

1273
01:09:05,950 --> 01:09:08,370
I have worked very, very,

1274
01:09:08,370 --> 01:09:13,370
very hard to foster good
relationships with the local media

1275
01:09:14,260 --> 01:09:16,423
and with the city of Pittsburgh.

1276
01:09:18,453 --> 01:09:20,423
I want to keep it that way.

1277
01:09:25,315 --> 01:09:28,630
- [Panelist] I've heard at
least one opinion up there

1278
01:09:28,630 --> 01:09:31,340
that the physical aspect
seems more prevalent,

1279
01:09:31,340 --> 01:09:33,420
the sexual aspect.

1280
01:09:33,420 --> 01:09:36,963
- Why do you think, where do
you think it originated from?

1281
01:09:36,963 --> 01:09:38,200
- If you're going to put all your effort

1282
01:09:38,200 --> 01:09:40,840
into one little piece, you
want to make sure it sells,

1283
01:09:40,840 --> 01:09:44,250
and the one that's sure to
sell is that hot steamy one.

1284
01:09:44,250 --> 01:09:46,000
- On the internet, it's horrible,

1285
01:09:46,000 --> 01:09:51,000
'cause like you cannot find
any good, normal furry art.

1286
01:09:51,430 --> 01:09:53,040
- You go into the ConFurence art show,

1287
01:09:53,040 --> 01:09:55,760
and even in the general audience section,

1288
01:09:55,760 --> 01:09:57,690
there's stuff that I
wouldn't show a child.

1289
01:09:57,690 --> 01:09:59,530
or my mother or any of my friends

1290
01:09:59,530 --> 01:10:00,823
outside furry fandom.

1291
01:10:01,910 --> 01:10:04,453
- I mean, sex sells everywhere.

1292
01:10:04,453 --> 01:10:09,453
You look in any subculture,
mainstream subculture,

1293
01:10:09,560 --> 01:10:12,370
goth, furry, anywhere.

1294
01:10:12,370 --> 01:10:15,000
- Not to the extreme extent

1295
01:10:15,000 --> 01:10:17,530
that it is portrayed
and pushed and produced

1296
01:10:17,530 --> 01:10:18,863
in furry fandom.

1297
01:10:28,180 --> 01:10:29,013
- Next, please.

1298
01:10:31,740 --> 01:10:34,460
- We started getting problems with people

1299
01:10:34,460 --> 01:10:38,853
trying to sabotage the
convention pretty early on.

1300
01:10:41,596 --> 01:10:43,150
You had to chalk this up to the fact

1301
01:10:43,150 --> 01:10:45,590
that people didn't like Rodney and I,

1302
01:10:45,590 --> 01:10:48,433
especially because we were a couple.

1303
01:10:49,330 --> 01:10:52,320
They naturally assumed our main interest

1304
01:10:52,320 --> 01:10:56,993
was have gathering of
like-minded people for sex.

1305
01:10:58,234 --> 01:11:02,484
And a lot of these rumors
were strung on for years.

1306
01:11:22,200 --> 01:11:25,440
- And then a Bay Area, furry convention

1307
01:11:25,440 --> 01:11:26,740
was gonna to happen in January.

1308
01:11:26,740 --> 01:11:31,740
This same time ours had
happened for nearly 10 years.

1309
01:11:32,840 --> 01:11:35,253
So we decided to change our dates.

1310
01:11:39,980 --> 01:11:42,000
A lot of the fans from San Diego said,

1311
01:11:42,000 --> 01:11:43,410
how about the Town and Country?

1312
01:11:43,410 --> 01:11:45,340
We've been having science
fiction conventions

1313
01:11:45,340 --> 01:11:46,660
there for years.

1314
01:11:46,660 --> 01:11:48,320
So I went and talked to the hotel

1315
01:11:48,320 --> 01:11:50,397
and I cut a deal with them.

1316
01:11:50,397 --> 01:11:55,090
But we tried have our planning
meetings in San Diego.

1317
01:11:55,090 --> 01:11:57,493
The staff from up here would not come.

1318
01:11:58,770 --> 01:11:59,920
They wouldn't drive it.

1319
01:12:00,780 --> 01:12:02,740
And more and more of the responsibility

1320
01:12:02,740 --> 01:12:04,370
fell on me and Rodney.

1321
01:12:04,370 --> 01:12:06,133
And it was taking all my time.

1322
01:12:08,160 --> 01:12:09,580
- [Radio] ...by all the flood water.

1323
01:12:09,580 --> 01:12:11,290
- As the nail in the coffin,

1324
01:12:11,290 --> 01:12:13,200
we had the worst April weather

1325
01:12:13,200 --> 01:12:15,693
they've ever had in San Diego in 20 years.

1326
01:12:16,979 --> 01:12:19,573
It was actually hailing in San Diego.

1327
01:12:21,440 --> 01:12:24,423
Attendance was down by
at least 200 people.

1328
01:12:25,380 --> 01:12:28,430
When I had the staff meeting
at the end of the convention,

1329
01:12:28,430 --> 01:12:31,000
I said, okay, I have worked with Rodney,

1330
01:12:31,000 --> 01:12:35,173
ran this convention from zero to 10.

1331
01:12:37,410 --> 01:12:39,663
I am stepping down.

1332
01:12:41,540 --> 01:12:44,110
People looked around for
someone to replace me

1333
01:12:44,110 --> 01:12:47,710
and the gentleman who had been
doing our daily newsletter,

1334
01:12:47,710 --> 01:12:49,713
stood up and said, I will take it over.

1335
01:12:50,577 --> 01:12:51,777
And everyone said great.

1336
01:12:56,300 --> 01:12:58,573
I guess it was in 2003.

1337
01:12:59,470 --> 01:13:02,480
He basically stood up at the
closing ceremonies and said,

1338
01:13:02,480 --> 01:13:05,823
I am officially closing
ConFurence forever.

1339
01:13:07,730 --> 01:13:10,320
He had told us that he
had trademarked the name

1340
01:13:10,320 --> 01:13:12,230
and that nobody else could ever have

1341
01:13:12,230 --> 01:13:14,170
a convention called ConFurence.

1342
01:13:21,410 --> 01:13:22,970
- I feel strange saying this,

1343
01:13:22,970 --> 01:13:24,633
but I expected it to get bigger.

1344
01:13:26,880 --> 01:13:29,450
I just had this dream in my head

1345
01:13:29,450 --> 01:13:32,213
of everything kind of coming together,

1346
01:13:33,130 --> 01:13:34,760
but we're going into an era

1347
01:13:34,760 --> 01:13:38,770
where people are more about
breaking apart communities

1348
01:13:38,770 --> 01:13:42,170
rather than coming together
into big communities.

1349
01:13:42,170 --> 01:13:46,513
And unfortunately, there's furry, too.

1350
01:13:53,690 --> 01:13:55,810
- Conventions were kind of viewed

1351
01:13:55,810 --> 01:13:57,730
by their host hotels and their host cities

1352
01:13:57,730 --> 01:14:00,400
as, what is this stuff?

1353
01:14:00,400 --> 01:14:01,810
Some folk got together.

1354
01:14:01,810 --> 01:14:04,080
They called themselves the Burned Furs

1355
01:14:04,080 --> 01:14:09,080
having been burned by this
image that was being projected.

1356
01:14:10,530 --> 01:14:14,520
The Burned Furs were out
to clean up the fandom,

1357
01:14:14,520 --> 01:14:19,520
get rid of all of that sex related stuff.

1358
01:14:20,110 --> 01:14:24,620
Now, I kind of agreed in
principle with that concept.

1359
01:14:24,620 --> 01:14:27,610
We okay, we can have fun,

1360
01:14:27,610 --> 01:14:30,800
but can we do it over there,
where people aren't looking?

1361
01:14:30,800 --> 01:14:32,820
- And I thought, hey, this
seems like a good idea.

1362
01:14:32,820 --> 01:14:34,330
Clean up fandom, why not?

1363
01:14:34,330 --> 01:14:38,300
But it was to the extreme.

1364
01:14:38,300 --> 01:14:41,720
- I've seen this fandom to
generate from a very nice thing

1365
01:14:41,720 --> 01:14:44,780
into a endless parade of human debris.

1366
01:14:44,780 --> 01:14:46,063
Thank you very much.

1367
01:14:46,063 --> 01:14:47,027
- This is Limbaugh.
(panelists clap)

1368
01:14:47,027 --> 01:14:51,720
- The Burned Furs felt
that there were people

1369
01:14:51,720 --> 01:14:54,320
in fur fandom that they did not like

1370
01:14:54,320 --> 01:14:58,223
who should be somehow
pushed out of the fandom.

1371
01:14:59,210 --> 01:15:02,737
- Particularly people
who like Rodney and I,

1372
01:15:02,737 --> 01:15:07,737
who were gay or bi and
demonstratively so at conventions.

1373
01:15:09,780 --> 01:15:11,670
Hanging out with their boyfriend,

1374
01:15:11,670 --> 01:15:13,420
cuddling on the couch or something.

1375
01:15:14,870 --> 01:15:18,163
What if, what if a
underage person sees that?

1376
01:15:20,570 --> 01:15:23,120
- So this group wanted
to do something about it

1377
01:15:23,120 --> 01:15:26,773
and they had a manifesto
of cleaning up the fandom.

1378
01:15:28,440 --> 01:15:29,870
No one was complaining

1379
01:15:29,870 --> 01:15:32,600
when all of the art was female pinups

1380
01:15:33,900 --> 01:15:35,773
and heterosexual couples.

1381
01:15:37,070 --> 01:15:38,290
It was okay.

1382
01:15:38,290 --> 01:15:42,100
- And ultimately the pushback
against porn and adult content

1383
01:15:42,100 --> 01:15:47,100
in furry is an attempt to
push LGBT furs out of furry.

1384
01:15:47,260 --> 01:15:51,510
- Somehow Mark and I were at fault

1385
01:15:51,510 --> 01:15:56,510
for the appearance of LGBT
people in among furry fandom,

1386
01:15:57,490 --> 01:16:01,013
which if we wanted to, we
wouldn't have known how.

1387
01:16:08,780 --> 01:16:12,810
Furry fandom has attracted every stripe

1388
01:16:12,810 --> 01:16:14,970
of the political spectrum.

1389
01:16:14,970 --> 01:16:18,110
Although we could all sit
around and discuss Donald Duck,

1390
01:16:18,110 --> 01:16:20,880
if we got into talking
about whether or not

1391
01:16:20,880 --> 01:16:23,050
there should be gay marriage allowed,

1392
01:16:23,050 --> 01:16:25,473
there would be bottles being thrown.

1393
01:16:27,940 --> 01:16:31,630
- It's interesting how this
entire thing got sidetracked,

1394
01:16:31,630 --> 01:16:34,103
essentially got completely sidetracked.

1395
01:16:47,810 --> 01:16:50,320
- The current alt-right problem

1396
01:16:50,320 --> 01:16:53,624
in furry fandom is the
current alt-right problem

1397
01:16:53,624 --> 01:16:55,440
in the United States,

1398
01:16:55,440 --> 01:16:57,310
which is the current alt-right problem.

1399
01:16:57,310 --> 01:16:59,130
In Western civilization,

1400
01:16:59,130 --> 01:17:00,610
- You are seeing more politics

1401
01:17:00,610 --> 01:17:02,150
than you've ever seen before get in.

1402
01:17:02,150 --> 01:17:04,060
I think once you've got the
Trump administration in,

1403
01:17:04,060 --> 01:17:05,860
you saw a lot of furries become

1404
01:17:05,860 --> 01:17:07,600
much more politically active,

1405
01:17:07,600 --> 01:17:10,560
and that's made it more difficult
for convention organizers

1406
01:17:10,560 --> 01:17:13,060
to know what they should
and shouldn't respond to.

1407
01:17:17,810 --> 01:17:22,013
- We have a pocket of individuals here,

1408
01:17:22,013 --> 01:17:26,880
intertwining with the
larger online community

1409
01:17:26,880 --> 01:17:27,730
of the alt-right.

1410
01:17:28,890 --> 01:17:31,783
Entangled with people that represent

1411
01:17:31,783 --> 01:17:35,653
a hate message towards
marginalized individuals.

1412
01:17:37,550 --> 01:17:41,903
- Different conventions have
had politics take them down.

1413
01:17:44,310 --> 01:17:46,920
- For the furry community,
that's pretty bad

1414
01:17:46,920 --> 01:17:49,253
'cause a lot of us are LGBTIA.

1415
01:17:50,840 --> 01:17:52,340
I don't think that I would have been

1416
01:17:52,340 --> 01:17:53,620
the person that I am today

1417
01:17:53,620 --> 01:17:55,293
if I didn't have furry cons.

1418
01:17:56,510 --> 01:17:57,373
No doubt.

1419
01:17:58,452 --> 01:18:00,990
- Thank you for this year.

1420
01:18:00,990 --> 01:18:02,790
Thank you for everything up to this year.

1421
01:18:02,790 --> 01:18:05,190
And we'll see you tomorrow.

1422
01:18:05,190 --> 01:18:09,273
We'll see you next year and good evening.

1423
01:18:10,490 --> 01:18:13,240
(audience claps)

1424
01:18:25,970 --> 01:18:27,637
- [Attendee] Hi mom.

1425
01:18:34,170 --> 01:18:37,330
- Well, early on I had encountered people

1426
01:18:37,330 --> 01:18:40,460
who said I came to the convention

1427
01:18:41,311 --> 01:18:45,213
and I walked into the
lobby and I felt I'm home.

1428
01:18:47,420 --> 01:18:48,913
I'm finally home.

1429
01:18:52,600 --> 01:18:56,653
They found their family,
they found their people,

1430
01:18:58,030 --> 01:19:03,030
they found their culture, and
that aspect has not changed.

1431
01:19:06,378 --> 01:19:09,295
(crowd chattering)

1432
01:19:26,190 --> 01:19:27,720
- Once I'm committed to something,

1433
01:19:27,720 --> 01:19:29,040
I don't want to let it go.

1434
01:19:29,040 --> 01:19:30,690
I can't let it go until the dies.

1435
01:19:31,650 --> 01:19:34,660
We've all grown as a community together,

1436
01:19:34,660 --> 01:19:36,220
but we want to make sure that

1437
01:19:37,110 --> 01:19:39,963
what we're doing now is what
the community wants now.

1438
01:19:40,980 --> 01:19:43,080
And I know if we lose these conventions,

1439
01:19:43,080 --> 01:19:45,090
we'll lose a lot of our community.

1440
01:19:45,090 --> 01:19:47,690
We have younger people
coming into the fandom

1441
01:19:47,690 --> 01:19:50,870
and they see how open everybody
is and they deserve that.

1442
01:19:50,870 --> 01:19:53,380
They deserve the
opportunities that we have

1443
01:19:53,380 --> 01:19:55,940
or that we didn't have
when we were younger.

1444
01:19:55,940 --> 01:19:58,150
- We can create environments
where people are safe,

1445
01:19:58,150 --> 01:20:00,770
where we don't overreact,
where we're not dramatic

1446
01:20:01,700 --> 01:20:04,540
and just try to be in the best interest

1447
01:20:04,540 --> 01:20:06,900
of our attendees overall,
and let them have

1448
01:20:06,900 --> 01:20:09,233
the environment they
can to be they wanna be.

1449
01:20:11,347 --> 01:20:12,470
- A lot of the negativity

1450
01:20:12,470 --> 01:20:14,680
comes from these big voices online.

1451
01:20:14,680 --> 01:20:17,100
And when you take it into perspective,

1452
01:20:17,100 --> 01:20:18,470
there's a thousand other people

1453
01:20:18,470 --> 01:20:20,348
that are having a good time.

1454
01:20:20,348 --> 01:20:21,680
I couldn't let it go.

1455
01:20:21,680 --> 01:20:23,283
I would, I would feel so guilty.

1456
01:20:32,910 --> 01:20:34,958
I think this year went really well.

1457
01:20:34,958 --> 01:20:37,433
2,700 attendees.

1458
01:20:38,590 --> 01:20:40,603
We raised $15,000 for charity.

1459
01:20:41,780 --> 01:20:43,430
- For Denver, we have
Freedom Service Dogs,

1460
01:20:43,430 --> 01:20:45,880
where last year we raised $15,000.

1461
01:20:45,880 --> 01:20:48,080
So they can have an awning for the dogs

1462
01:20:48,080 --> 01:20:49,560
when they go outside so it didn't burn

1463
01:20:49,560 --> 01:20:50,393
their paw pads.

1464
01:20:50,393 --> 01:20:52,210
when they're going from the
indoor training facilities

1465
01:20:52,210 --> 01:20:53,940
to the outdoor kennels,

1466
01:20:53,940 --> 01:20:55,880
- [Bubbles] We raise
as much money as we can

1467
01:20:55,880 --> 01:20:57,860
for the charity we choose.

1468
01:20:57,860 --> 01:20:59,980
We try to pick them locally

1469
01:20:59,980 --> 01:21:01,943
and they're usually animal related.

1470
01:21:06,830 --> 01:21:09,940
- I really feel like I
owe a lot to the community

1471
01:21:09,940 --> 01:21:12,110
just because it's taught me so much.

1472
01:21:12,110 --> 01:21:13,470
It's made me become much more

1473
01:21:13,470 --> 01:21:15,560
of a open and understanding person.

1474
01:21:15,560 --> 01:21:18,510
- And we are, I think,
outgrowing those stereotypes.

1475
01:21:18,510 --> 01:21:21,170
I think we're becoming
appreciated for ourselves.

1476
01:21:21,170 --> 01:21:22,540
- Artists are really like the backbone

1477
01:21:22,540 --> 01:21:23,780
of so much of what happens

1478
01:21:23,780 --> 01:21:25,870
because that's how we're representing

1479
01:21:25,870 --> 01:21:27,100
these characters at all.

1480
01:21:27,100 --> 01:21:29,550
- I remember at the first few conventions,

1481
01:21:29,550 --> 01:21:31,640
no, nobody's ever gonna make
a living off of doing this.

1482
01:21:31,640 --> 01:21:34,530
You're crazy to think
that, and here we are today

1483
01:21:34,530 --> 01:21:36,580
and there's probably hundreds of artists

1484
01:21:36,580 --> 01:21:39,023
making some or all of
their living off of this.

1485
01:21:46,834 --> 01:21:48,560
- I think the fandom
has made my life better.

1486
01:21:48,560 --> 01:21:49,960
- I probably wouldn't even have

1487
01:21:49,960 --> 01:21:51,620
a quarter of the life that I do now.

1488
01:21:51,620 --> 01:21:53,200
- I'd have a different career.

1489
01:21:53,200 --> 01:21:55,130
I don't know if I'd be happy.

1490
01:21:55,130 --> 01:21:58,700
- I'd be just a nobody in a crowd.

1491
01:21:58,700 --> 01:22:00,010
- I would never have met my husband.

1492
01:22:00,010 --> 01:22:02,130
I would never have met my best friends.

1493
01:22:02,130 --> 01:22:05,260
- Every single one of my
closest friends is a furry.

1494
01:22:05,260 --> 01:22:10,230
- Just thinking about not
having that experience is hard.

1495
01:22:10,230 --> 01:22:13,510
- Not having that, I don't know what I do.

1496
01:22:13,510 --> 01:22:15,250
- I don't really want to think about

1497
01:22:15,250 --> 01:22:16,750
because it seems like it would be

1498
01:22:16,750 --> 01:22:18,763
a very, very dark road to go down.

1499
01:22:22,660 --> 01:22:26,103
- We have our typical
story we have about fandom.

1500
01:22:27,240 --> 01:22:28,130
- What is furry fandom?

1501
01:22:28,130 --> 01:22:29,940
Oh, it's a bunch of guys who
like sitting around drawing.

1502
01:22:29,940 --> 01:22:32,700
- And a lot of the films
were really popular.

1503
01:22:32,700 --> 01:22:35,490
- That was the first convention.

1504
01:22:35,490 --> 01:22:38,240
(crowd chatters)

1505
01:22:46,310 --> 01:22:48,613
- [Mark] Our fandom is based on a concept,

1506
01:22:49,557 --> 01:22:52,120
and that concept isn't going away.

1507
01:22:52,120 --> 01:22:54,310
- I go around to conventions

1508
01:22:54,310 --> 01:22:57,100
and I look at the fur suit parade.

1509
01:22:57,100 --> 01:22:59,340
I look at the dances.

1510
01:22:59,340 --> 01:23:03,150
I look at the dealers' rooms
and how big they've gotten

1511
01:23:03,150 --> 01:23:05,460
and I'll admit it.

1512
01:23:05,460 --> 01:23:08,300
I sometimes will walk
around kind of going.

1513
01:23:08,300 --> 01:23:11,140
Yeah, yeah.

1514
01:23:11,140 --> 01:23:13,393
I was involved with starting this, yeah.

1515
01:23:16,020 --> 01:23:17,700
- We're still in it.

1516
01:23:17,700 --> 01:23:20,180
And we're probably not
going to get out of it.

1517
01:23:20,180 --> 01:23:22,030
I don't intend to ever get out of it.

1518
01:23:25,750 --> 01:23:29,130
I think the fandom is something

1519
01:23:29,130 --> 01:23:31,763
I'm the most proud of in my life.

1520
01:23:33,460 --> 01:23:36,940
- When people are having
fun at a convention,

1521
01:23:36,940 --> 01:23:41,940
at a meetup, online, or just two people

1522
01:23:42,140 --> 01:23:44,090
